Although the position after 10.....Be7 is on my opening databases, I can't find this queen move on them. Presumably the idea is throwing the queen over to the king-side to support a pawn advance there. I don't think it turns out particularly well for white.

Played with the idea of preventing him permanently occupying d5 with a piece. If he plays Nd5 I can take it. He can't take back with the rook, so he has to take with the pawn and then my weakness on d6 is shielded by his pawn on d5. They is also the chance of an attack on a2. I'm quite happy with this position for black.
